name: Recontacting for additional sampling
definition: Willingness to be recontacted to collect additional material or data from the patient.

name: Recontacting for incidental findings
definition: Willingness to be recontacted when new knowledge regarding incidental findings becomes available to benefit the patient.

name: Recontacting for diagnostic question
definition: Willingness to be recontacted when new knowledge regarding the diagnostic question becomes available to benefit the patient.
